editorialNotes.standard: Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedand Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether youre assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the successor the rough edgesof your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.

editorialNotes.tagline: Interact with the power of nature
editorialNotes.standard: Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thats delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

editorialNotes.standard: What are those towers that touch the sky? Tinybops awesome sandbox teaches kids the fun wayby letting them build, watch, and play. As they add floors and test the effects of plumbing problems and earthquakes, they're actually learning basic design and engineering principles. Amazing details aboundfrom all the busy little inhabitants to the full-blown skyline you can make.
